                " \n \nTEAM LEADER: AIRTIME RADIO\nReporting line: airtime manager: RADIO\nPosition id: 600200144\nScale code: 401\n \nCLOSING DATE: 22 OCTOBER 2023\nMAIN PURPOSE OF POSITION\n To lead, support, guide, and instil a client-centric, service-based culture into a team ensuring accountability for delivery of services on SABC platforms. Delivering excellent client service and developing strong relationships with internal and external stakeholders.\n \nKEY ACCOUNTABILITIES\nManage the process of airtime schedule and ensure timeous delivery of services.\nProcessing of all requests from approval to delivery.\nProvide weekly/monthly operational reports to the Airtime Manager.\nFocus on mitigation factors for revenue loss reduction attributable to system   or staff inefficiencies.\nWork in conjunction with linear and non-linear platforms to best maximise break patterns and audience efficiencies.\nConduct schedule quality checks and ensure transmission readiness.\nDevelop the capability of team members on processes and systems.\nEnsure the teams operate within the SABC\u2019 standard policies and regulations.\nMonitor and ensure effective use of available resources.\nEffective implementation of a Performance Management System in accordance with organizational policy and procedures.\nMentoring and coaching for succession planning.\nDevelop business unit staff members.\nProvide direction on the retention and attraction of staff.\nManage the employee relations to ensure conducive and productive working environment.\nOversee the implementation of organizational development initiative i.e. Wellness, Employment Equity, Career Progression, Talent Management, and Human Capital Planning etc.\nDirect, manage and develop the Airtime Management Team \nAbility to troubleshoot and find solutions under pressure.\nResponsible for the day to day functioning of the team.\nProvide support in reaching the division\u2019s yield management objectives, through optimal inventory management in line with programme price.\nEstablish and maintain internal and external client relations through excellent client service.\nAbility to manage relationships across hierarchy and unit boundaries.\nWillingness to share information and provide training to stakeholders.\nOptimise inventory in line with ICASA mandates and channel restrictions.\nManage Compliance to legislation mandates and internal policies.\nAdherence to file plan management processes/system\n(Governance and risk).\nImplement Risk Management Plan and Internal Risk Audit.  \nReview and Report on the achievement and challenges of business units objectives. (Monthly, quarterly and annually).\nWell-developed knowledge of governance and organizational processes.\n \nREQUIREMENTS\nNational Diploma (NQF 6) in Marketing/Advertising/Communications/Media studies / Information Technology or equivalent\n5 years\u2019 experience in sales operations/ bookings/ scheduling and traffic in media broadcasting.  Knowledge of booking and planning systems as used in the advertising and broadcasting industry.\nLeadership development qualification will be an added advantage.\nCustomer service oriented\nStrategic management.\nBusiness acumen.\nProject management.\nPersuasion and negotiations skills.\nUnderstanding of different sporting code and legislations.\nKnowledge and understanding of the advertising industry, trends and developments and SABC brands.\nUnderstanding of applicable legislative frameworks and regulations.\nBe a team player.\nBusiness Writing Skills\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
